      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOOD VIBES (4) missed by 1.8L just five days ago when running in a CL5 over the 1200m at York in a strong performance. She loves this course and distance and Cheung hops back on board claiming 2kg. Watch for her late in the race. PRETTY DEVINE (1) led them up in a BM44+ last start at York and couldn't hold on when beaten by 1.8L as the race favourite. Webster remains in the saddle and she'll carry less weight with the rise in grade. Drawn the inside again and will be tough to mow down. IMAPAGETHREE GIRL (5) hasn't been far away her past couple, beaten 1.2L at Kalgoorlie just eight days ago. Tsang hops on board and while she hasn't won for a while, she's right on the cusp based on her last start. G'DAY BLOKE (6) did little and finished 12 lengths from the winner in 13th over 1230m at Albany last start, a less impressive effort than his eighth at Pinjarra the run before. Has the talent to produce a better result. O'SO DEMANDING (7) won't be far away.",
